t, the harder it seems to be to keep aggro.  I realize that lower delay is important, so are procs that upset your target.  What else helps, besides taunt?  It seems to me that disarm -- even on mobs that don't have a weapon -- increases aggro.  And slam is definitely a taunter.  So far, I've just been focusing on trying to use those skills at the right time to keep aggro or get it back -- using disarm and slam when they're still on me, saving taunt for when they turn to the rogue.  What else seems to work?<br>
<br>
I'm curious, has anyone tried dual wielding split paw whips?  They are fast and proc stun which is a nice taunt -- haven't tried it but tempted to give it a shot. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I'm a mid-40's ogre warrior, if that makes a difference.<br>
<br>
