Blackguard of the 55th pilfer<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucoray.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Coray</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/2/01 12:02:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How do you keep aggro?</span><hr size=1> Yep, under the nuts.  Closer you are, typically the easier it is to keep the mob on you.  Also have the other people involved in the group or raid, hang back some and watch their own aggro.<br>
<br>
As various verant people have said, its the job of everyone to control their aggro so that it does what you want it to do, there isnt just one thing that you can necessarily do.<br>
<br>
Faster weapons help, better weapons, weapons that proc, proximity, etc.<br>
<br>
Experiment with taunting.  been awhile since i did exp, but I generally felt that using it even while I had aggro, helped me to keep aggro.  I could go into the reasons for that but I wont, just play with it and see if you can approach taunting differently. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ujaikarhalfelf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaikar HalfElf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.epicadventures.net/pic/covicon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Everybody's Favorite Hero</span><br>  Posts: 457<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/2/01 2:26:25 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.epicadventures.net/pic/jaikarphoto.jpg border=0></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How do you keep aggro?</span><hr size=1> The best way ta practice &quot;keepin' aggro&quot; is ta have yer group's weezard nuke yer foe as hard as they can right atta beginnin' o' battle while they runs in circles screamin' &quot;GIT IT OFF ME! GIT IT OFF ME!&quot;<br>
