<br>
usually wizards first, than the rangers. paladins usually with LoH's finish ahead of the mage pets by about 3 hits; than the 'chanters usually gate by now because the purple life bars of everyone else scares them because they're next . . .<br>
<br>
than just pick up where they left off. usually the critter is at half health, and, with a full tummy of eating everyone else. Cleric saves mana, and, no ear-aches of all the others screaming  &quot; Heal Me Heal Me . &quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ushoontokofhalas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ShoontokOfHalas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/2/01 2:49:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How do you keep aggro?</span><hr size=1> I actually keep gnoll hide lariat in my pack for fighting gating type casters and such when im not MT. Im level 53 Warrior and i hunt alot with a 59 Monk with epic fists, he almost always keeps aggro and there is nothing i can do. Actually he is better off taking hits then me cause his AC is much higher then mine and almost has the same number of HP as me. But when i pull out the gnoll whip and put Trochillic Skean in the off hand and when i have a nice dex buff, the mobs start getting really pissed at me.<br>
<br>
Shoontok <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukbern.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kbern</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/4/01 11:05:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How do you keep aggro?</span><hr size=1> My tank is only lvl 37 now but I have noticed if I pull, I can usually maintain aggro over even monks or SK's..good gear for my level.<br>
<br>
But if they pull, or get a head start on the mob, I cant retain aggro for any good length of time.<br>
<br>
The crappy thing is some players get a kick outa out taunting the tank, and dont realize that it is not an ego booster, but a proper tactic to let the main tank hold aggro.  SO you not only are fighting normally to get aggro with some classes, there are times where they are TRYING to maintain aggro...I just dont get it.<br>
<br>
Not class flaming here, just player flaming those who dont play thier class right. <p><HTML><BODY>
