border=0 alt="Image by FlamingText.com"></a>
<br>Image by <a href="http://www.flamingtext.com/ezb2.html">FlamingText.com</a>
</BODY></HTML></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udelane01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Delane01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/4/01 11:43:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How do you keep aggro?</span><hr size=1> Great low dly high dmg weapons with taunting procs...<br>
<br>
Something that is semi attainable by most....<br>
<br>
Frostbringer works great.<br>
<br>
High High High end...<br>
<br>
All our warriors have Septer of Destruction in main and Primal in off hand...<br>
<br>
Proximity...it does make a difference...  So warriors stay close...None warriors...bards, sk/pali, monks, stand at the very edge of atk range.<br>
<br>
Just because you have argo....dont stop taunting...  Don't know if disarm creates argo for sure or not...but just in case it does I also use disarm.<br>
<br>
Make sure non-tank that gets argo backs off and STOPS atking.<br>
<br>
Make sure tash, snare etc are done at appropriate times..not .01 seconds after you start atking.<br>
<br>
Pulling helps you build and keep argo...not always feasible.but its nice to ahve a start in building argo on the mob before others even join the hate list.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uarative.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arative</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/4/01 1:04:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How do you keep aggro?</span><hr size=1> I use a hammer of battle 17/25, main hand and axe of resistance 15/24 offhand. Not a fast combo but heavy hitting. I use a combination of taunt/disarm to gain agro. Never really had a problem maintaining agro with the group. But then again I usually group with people that know what they are doing. You know, monk's that FD when they get do get agro, rogues that evade. Casters that don't over nuke. Maybe I've been lucky to group with skilled players.<br>
<br>
It helps the warrior greatly when you group with players that know what they are doing. In the long run it saves time and mana.<br>
<br>
Arative<br>
58 warrior<br>
